6 An Act relating to crimes and punishments; amending
21 O.S. 2021, Section 856.3, which relates to gang-
7 related offenses; modifying reference to certain
offense; updating statutory language and references;
8 and providing an effective date.
9
10
11 BE IT ENACTED BY THE PEOPLE OF THE STATE OF OKLAHOMA:
12 SECTION 1. AMENDATORY 21 O.S. 2021, Section 856.3, is
13 amended to read as follows:
14 Section 856.3. Any person who attempts or commits a gang-
15 related offense as a condition of membership in a criminal street
16 gang or while in association with any criminal street gang or gang
17 member shall be guilty of a felony offense. Upon punishable upon
18 conviction, the violator shall be punished by incarceration
19 imprisonment in the custody of the Department of Corrections for a
20 term of five (5) years, which shall be in addition to any other
21 penalty imposed. For purposes of this section, “criminal street
22 gang” is defined by subsection F of Section 856 of Title 21 of the
23 Oklahoma Statutes this title and “gang-related offense” means those
24
ENGR. S. B. NO. 861 Page 1
1 offe nses enumerated in paragraphs 1 through 16 of subsection F of
2 Section 856 of Title 21 of the Oklahoma Statutes this title.
3 SECTION 2. This act shall become effective November 1, 2025.
4 Passed the Senate the 10th day of March, 2025.
